To whom it may concern,

Without admitting liability for the above-referenced debt, I am
offering to settle it on the following terms, conditioned in full on
your written agreement before any payment is made:

  1. I will pay $___________ (a partial amount of the alleged
     balance) by cashier's check or money order, within fifteen (15)
     days of receipt of your countersigned agreement.

  2. In exchange, your organization will:
       (a) accept the payment as full and final settlement of the
           above-referenced debt;
       (b) cease all collection activity related to this debt;
       (c) instruct each consumer reporting agency to which you have
           reported this debt to delete the tradeline in its
           entirety — not simply mark it "paid" or "settled" — under
           your authority as a furnisher (15 U.S.C. §1681s-2);
       (d) confirm in writing that you will not sell, assign, or
           transfer this debt to any other party.

  3. This letter is not an acknowledgement of the debt, does not
     waive any defense, and does not restart any statute of
     limitations under any applicable state or federal law.

If these terms are acceptable, please countersign below and return a
copy to me at the address above. If you cannot accept, please respond
in writing with the specific terms you would accept.

Sincerely,


